  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And then I think Jula came, this woman came, and took me to her flat, to her tiny flat with one room and something, which was right next to the Umschlagplatz on the other side of the wall of course, but very near Umschlagplatz in a very not highly thought of part of Warsaw, with all kinds of-- with criminal elements living around, and lumpenproletariat, and so on.",
      "word_count": 68
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Lumpenproletariat are people who-- what is now called in English under class, people who are not exactly fully employed, who are not workers, who live from hand to mouth, who are maybe stealing, or maybe doing some dealing in stolen things, or maybe doing some other doubtful things.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But, basically, have not-- or maybe working for a while, and then not a-- anyway, the lowest social class that exists, practically.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So lumpenproletariat now really made some of their income out of looking for Jews who are trying to hide.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, indeed, only few days later, we were walking near Jula's flat somewhere with my mother and with Jula.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I still must have been completely out of my mind, because after all, after spending three years or thereabouts, or two and a half years, in the ghetto, suddenly getting out of there, and being among normal people, so to say, was something completely incredible.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I think that one said, if one could recognize-- one had to be able to-- on the Aryan side of Warsaw, you had to speak Polish perfectly.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You had to look like an Aryan.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You had to look like-- you couldn't have typical Jewish looks, because that was no good.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
